{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Number","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects\">Standard-Objekte</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a></strong></li><li data-default-state=\"open\"><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/EPSILON\"><code>Number.EPSILON</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MAX_SAFE_INTEGER\"><code>Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MAX_VALUE\"><code>Number.MAX_VALUE</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MIN_SAFE_INTEGER\"><code>Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MIN_VALUE\"><code>Number.MIN_VALUE</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NaN\"><code>Number.NaN</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NEGATIVE_INFINITY\"><code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a></li></ol></li><li data-default-state=\"open\"><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isFinite\"><code>Number.isFinite()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isInteger\"><code>Number.isInteger()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isNaN\"><code>Number.isNaN()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isSafeInteger\"><code>Number.isSafeInteger()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseFloat\"><code>Number.parseFloat()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseInt\"><code>Number.parseInt()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toExponential\"><code>Number.prototype.toExponential()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toFixed\"><code>Number.prototype.toFixed()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toLocaleString\"><code>Number.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toPrecision\"><code>Number.prototype.toPrecision()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString\"><code>Number.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/valueOf\"><code>Number.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong>Vererbung:</strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function\"><code>Function</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/arguments\"><code>Function.prototype.arguments</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/caller\"><code>Function.prototype.caller</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/displayName\"><code>Function.prototype.displayName</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/length\"><code>Function.prototype.length</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/name\"><code>Function.prototype.name</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/prototype\"><code>Function.prototype.prototype</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/apply\"><code>Function.prototype.apply()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/bind\"><code>Function.prototype.bind()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/call\"><code>Function.prototype.call()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/toString\"><code>Function.prototype.toString()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Das JavaScript Objekt <strong><code>Number</code></strong> ist ein Container Objekt (Wrapper Objekt), welches das Arbeiten mit numerischen Werten erlaubt. Ein <code>Number</code> Objekt wird erzeugt indem der <code>Number()</code> Konstruktor verwendet wird.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\">new Number(value);</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"value\"><code>value</code></dt>\n <dd>Ein&nbsp;numerischer Wert, der als Objekt erstellt werden soll.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Die hauptsächlichen Nutzungen des <code>Number</code> Objektes sind:</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Wenn der Parameter nicht zu einer Nummer konvertiert werden kann, wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>&nbsp;zurückgegeben.</li>\n <li>In einem&nbsp;nicht-Konstruktor Kontext (z. B. ohne den <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/new\"><code>new</code></a> Operator) führt <code>Number</code> zu einer Typkonvertierung.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Eigenschaften","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"number.epsilon\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/EPSILON\"><code>Number.EPSILON</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Das kleinste Intervall zwischen zwei repräsentierbaren Zahlen.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.max_safe_integer\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MAX_SAFE_INTEGER\"><code>Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Die größte sichere Ganzzahl in JavaScript (2<sup>53</sup> -1).</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.max_value\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MAX_VALUE\"><code>Number.MAX_VALUE</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Die größte repräsentierbare Zahl.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.min_safe_integer\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MIN_SAFE_INTEGER\"><code>Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Die kleinste sichere Ganzzahl in JavaScript (-(2<sup>53</sup> -1)).</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.min_value\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MIN_VALUE\"><code>Number.MIN_VALUE</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Die kleinste positive repräsentierbare Zahl. Das ist die positive Zahl, die am nächsten an <code>0</code> ist (aber nicht <code>0</code> ist).</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.nan\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NaN\"><code>Number.NaN</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Spezieller \"keine Zahl\" Wert.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.negative_infinity\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NEGATIVE_INFINITY\"><code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Spezieller Wert welcher negativ Unendlich repräsentiert; wird bei einem Overflow zurückgegeben.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.positive_infinity\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Spezieller Wert welcher positiv Unendlich repräsentiert; wird bei einem Overflow zurückgegeben.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.prototype_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number.prototype</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>\n <div id=\"gt-src-tools\">\n <div id=\"tts_button\"><span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"de\"><span>Ermöglicht das Hinzufügen</span> <span>von</span> <span>Eigenschaften</span> <span>zu</span> <span>einem</span> <span><code>Number</code> Objekt</span></span></div>\n </div>\n </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methoden","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"number.isnan\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isNaN\"><code>Number.isNaN()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Gibt an, ob&nbsp;der übergebene&nbsp;Wert <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> ist.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.isfinite\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isFinite\"><code>Number.isFinite()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Gibt an, ob der übergebene&nbsp;Wert&nbsp;eine endliche Zahl ist.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.isinteger\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isInteger\"><code>Number.isInteger()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Gibt an, ob der übergebene&nbsp;Wert eine ganze Zahl ist.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.issafeinteger\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isSafeInteger\"><code>Number.isSafeInteger()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Gibt an, ob der der übergebene&nbsp;Wert eine sichere ganze Zahl ist&nbsp;(eine ganze Zahl zwischen -(2<sup>53</sup> -1) und 2<sup>53</sup> -1).</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.tointeger_dies_ist_eine_veraltete_api_und_es_wird_nicht_mehr_garantiert_dass_sie_funktioniert\"><s class=\"obsoleteElement\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"Die Beschreibung hierüber wurde bisher noch nicht geschrieben. Bitte überlege, mitzuwirken!\"><code>Number.toInteger()</code></a> <svg class=\"icon obsolete\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" role=\"img\">\n    <title>Dies ist eine veraltete API und es wird nicht mehr garantiert, dass sie funktioniert.</title>\n    <path d=\"M38.75 78.13V36.88A1.85 1.85 0 0036.88 35h-3.75a1.85 1.85 0 00-1.88 1.88v41.25A1.85 1.85 0 0033.13 80h3.75a1.85 1.85 0 001.87-1.87zm15 0V36.88A1.85 1.85 0 0051.88 35h-3.75a1.85 1.85 0 00-1.88 1.88v41.25A1.85 1.85 0 0048.13 80h3.75a1.85 1.85 0 001.87-1.87zm15 0V36.88A1.85 1.85 0 0066.88 35h-3.75a1.85 1.85 0 00-1.88 1.88v41.25A1.85 1.85 0 0063.13 80h3.75a1.85 1.85 0 001.87-1.87zM36.88 20h26.25l-2.82-6.85a2.35 2.35 0 00-1-.65H40.74a2 2 0 00-1 .65zm54.37 1.88v3.75a1.85 1.85 0 01-1.87 1.87h-5.63v55.55c0 6.44-4.22 12-9.37 12H25.63c-5.16 0-9.38-5.27-9.38-11.72V27.5h-5.62a1.85 1.85 0 01-1.88-1.83v-3.8A1.85 1.85 0 0110.63 20h18.1l4.1-9.78A9.12 9.12 0 0140.63 5h18.75a9.1 9.1 0 017.79 5.22l4.1 9.78h18.11a1.85 1.85 0 011.87 1.87z\"></path>\n</svg></s></dt>\n <dd><s class=\"obsoleteElement\">Wurde eingesetzt um eine Zahl zu einer ganzen Zahl zu konvertieren. Die Funktion wurde entfernt.</s></dd>\n <dt id=\"number.parsefloat\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseFloat\"><code>Number.parseFloat()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Der Wert ist der gleiche wie bei der <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/parseFloat\"><code>parseFloat()</code></a> Funktion des globalen Objektes.</dd>\n <dt id=\"number.parseint\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseInt\"><code>Number.parseInt()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Der Wert ist der gleiche wie bei der <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/parseInt\"><code>parseInt()</code></a> Funktion des globalen Objektes.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"number_instances","title":"<code>Number</code> Instanzen","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Alle Instanzen von <code>Number</code> erben von <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number.prototype</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>. Das Prototyp Objekt des <code>Number</code> Konstruktors kann verändert werden, um alle Instanzen von <code>Number</code> zu beeinflussen.</p>","titleAsText":"Number Instanzen"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods_of_number_instance","title":"Methoden","isH3":true,"content":"<div id=\"sect2\">{{page('/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/prototype', 'Methoden')}}</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_the_number_object_to_assign_values_to_numeric_variables","title":"Einsatz des <code>Number</code> Objektes&nbsp;zur Zuweisung von numerischen Variablen","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Das folgende Beispiel benutzt Eigenschaften des <code>Number</code> Objektes um Werte zu numerischen Variablen zuzuweisen:</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> biggestNum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">MAX_VALUE</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> smallestNum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">MIN_VALUE</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> infiniteNum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">POSITIVE_INFINITY</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> negInfiniteNum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">NEGATIVE_INFINITY</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> notANum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token number\">NaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz des Number Objektes zur Zuweisung von numerischen Variablen"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_number_to_convert_a_date_object","title":"Ganzzahlbereich von <code>Number</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Das folgende Beispiel zeigt die kleinste und größte Ganzzahl, welche mit <code>Number</code> Objekten repräsentiert werden kann (für Details siehe im ECMAScript Standard Kapitel <em><a href=\"https://tc39.github.io/ecma262/#sec-ecmascript-language-types-number-type\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">6.1.6 The Number Type</a></em>):</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> biggestInt <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">9007199254740992</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> smallestInt <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">9007199254740992</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Wenn Daten im JSON Format eingelesen werden und Ganzzahlen den oben gezeigten&nbsp;Bereich übersteigen, kann es passieren, dass Fehler beim Erstellen von <code>Number</code> Objekten auftreten. Mit dem Einsatz von <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>String</code></a> können solche Fehler umgangen werden.&nbsp;</p>","titleAsText":"Ganzzahlbereich von Number"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_number_to_convert_a_date_object_2","title":"Einsatz von <code>Number</code> zum Konvertieren eines <code>Date</code>&nbsp;Objekts","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Das folgende Beispiel konvertiert ein <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date\"><code>Date</code></a> Objekt in einen numerischen Wert. Dazu wird <code>Number</code> als Funktion verwendet:</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> d <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Date</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"December 17, 1995 03:24:00\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Ausgabe: \"819199440000\".</p>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von Number zum Konvertieren eines Date Objekts"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"konvertiertung_von_strings_zu_nummern","title":"Konvertiertung von Strings zu Nummern","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'123'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">// 123</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'12.3'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 12.3</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'123e-1'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// 12.3</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>        <span class=\"token comment\">// 0</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'0x11'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 17</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'0b11'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 3</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'0o11'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 9</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'foo'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'100a'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.1.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.7\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-number-objects\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>\n    <p>Neue Methoden und Properties hinzugefügt: <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/EPSILON\"><code>EPSILON</code></a>, <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isFinite\"><code>isFinite</code></a>, <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isInteger\"><code>isInteger</code></a>, <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isNaN\"><code>isNaN</code></a>, <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseFloat\"><code>parseFloat</code></a>, <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseInt\"><code>parseInt</code></a></p>\n   </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-number-objects\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Number.Number","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a></li>\n <li>Das globale Objekt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math\"><code>Math</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@maximus.koretskyi/javascripts-number-type-8d59199db1b6#.9whwe88tz\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Number type in&nbsp;details</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"description"},{"text":"Eigenschaften","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methoden","id":"methods"},{"text":"<code>Number</code> Instanzen","id":"number_instances"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Das JavaScript Objekt Number ist ein Container Objekt (Wrapper Objekt), welches das Arbeiten mit numerischen Werten erlaubt. Ein Number Objekt wird erzeugt indem der Number() Konstruktor verwendet wird.","popularity":0.0009,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Number","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Number","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Number","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Number","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Number","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Number","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Número","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Number","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Number","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Number","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/number","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blo